  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>2D Mensuration is the branch of mathematics that deals with the measurement of various flat geometric figures and shapes. This includes calculating areas and perimeters of two-dimensional shapes like squares, rectangles, circles, and triangles.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>This mathematical discipline primarily involves determining:</span></p><ol><li value=\"1\"><b><strong>Perimeter</strong></b><span>: The total boundary length of shapes.</span></li><li value=\"2\"><b><strong>Area</strong></b><span>: The surface coverage of plane figures.</span></li></ol><h2 id=\"mensuration-terminologies\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Mensuration Terminologies</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span>Here are the terms you will come across in 2D mensuration. We have provided the term, abbreviation, unit, and definition for easy understanding.</span></p><table><thead><tr><th style=\"text-align: center;\"><span>Terms</span></th><th style=\"text-align: center;\"><span>Abbreviation</span></th><th style=\"text-align: center;\"><span>Unit</span></th><th style=\"text-align: center;\"><span>Definition</span></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\"><b><strong>Area</strong></b></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span>A</span></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span>m</span><sup><span>2</span></sup><span>\u00a0or cm</span><sup><span>2</span></sup></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span>The surface that the closed form covers is known as the area.</span></td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\"><b><strong>Perimeter</strong></b></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span>P</span></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span>cm or m</span></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span>A perimeter is the length of the continuous line that encircles the specified figure.</span></td></tr></tbody></table><h3 id=\"mensuration-formula-for-2d-shapes\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Mensuration Formula For 2D Shapes</span></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The following table provides a list of all mensuration formulas for 2D shapes:</span></p><table><thead><tr><th><b><strong>Shape</strong></b></th><th style=\"text-align: center;\"><b><strong>Area (Square units)</strong></b></th><th style=\"text-align: center;\"><b><strong>Perimeter (units)</strong></b></th><th><b><strong>Figure</strong></b></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-square\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><strong>Square</strong></b></a></td><td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span>a</span><sup><span>2</span></sup></td><td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span>4a</span></td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Shapes-1\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250113153354144391/Shapes-1-100.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250113153354144391/Shapes-1.webp 250w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250113153354144391/Shapes-1-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250113153354144391/Shapes-1-200.webp 200w\" width=\"100\"/><figcaption>Square dimensions</figcaption></figure></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-rectangle\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><strong>Rectangle</strong></b></a></td><td><span>l \u00d7 b</span></td><td><span>2(l + b)</span></td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Shapes-2\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010319/Shapes-2-100.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010319/Shapes-2.webp 250w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010319/Shapes-2-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010319/Shapes-2-200.webp 200w\" width=\"100\"/><figcaption>Rectangle dimensions</figcaption></figure></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-circles\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><strong>Circle</strong></b></a></td><td><span>\u03c0r</span><sup><span>2</span></sup></td><td><span>2\u03c0r</span></td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Shapes-4\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010320/Shapes-4-100.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010320/Shapes-4.webp 250w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010320/Shapes-4-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010320/Shapes-4-200.webp 200w\" width=\"100\"/><figcaption>Circle with radius</figcaption></figure></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-scalene-triangle\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><b><strong>Scalene Triangle</strong></b></a></td><td><span>\u221a[s(s-a)(s-b)(s-c)],</span><br/><span>Where,</span><br/><span>s = (a+b+c)/2</span></td><td><span>a + b + c</span></td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Shapes-6\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010321/Shapes-6-100.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010321/Shapes-6.webp 250w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010321/Shapes-6-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010321/Shapes-6-200.webp 200w\" width=\"100\"/><figcaption>Scalene triangle dimensions</figcaption></figure></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-isosceles-triangle\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><b><strong>Isosceles Triangle</strong></b></a></td><td><span>\u00bd \u00d7 b \u00d7 h</span></td><td><span>2a + b</span></td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"2056957781\" height=\"74\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260331180458573490/2056957781-100.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260331180458573490/2056957781.webp 367w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260331180458573490/2056957781-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260331180458573490/2056957781-200.webp 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260331180458573490/2056957781-300.webp 300w\" width=\"100\"/><figcaption>Isosceles Triangle</figcaption></figure></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-equilateral-triangle\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><b><strong>Equilateral Triangle</strong></b></a></td><td><span>(\u221a3/4) \u00d7 a</span><sup><span>2</span></sup></td><td><span>3a</span></td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Shapes-7\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010322/Shapes-7-100.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010322/Shapes-7.webp 250w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010322/Shapes-7-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010322/Shapes-7-200.webp 200w\" width=\"100\"/><figcaption>Equilateral triangle dimensions</figcaption></figure></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-right-angled-triangle\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><strong>Right Angle Triangle</strong></b></a></td><td><span>\u00bd \u00d7 b \u00d7 h</span></td><td><span>b + hypotenuse + h</span></td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Shapes-5\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010320/Shapes-5-100.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010320/Shapes-5.webp 250w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010320/Shapes-5-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010320/Shapes-5-200.webp 200w\" width=\"100\"/><figcaption>Right Angle Triangle dimensions</figcaption></figure></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-rhombus\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><strong>Rhombus</strong></b></a></td><td><span>\u00bd \u00d7 d1 \u00d7 d2</span></td><td><span>4 \u00d7 side</span></td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Shapes-10\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010323/Shapes-10-100.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010323/Shapes-10.webp 250w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010323/Shapes-10-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010323/Shapes-10-200.webp 200w\" width=\"100\"/><figcaption>Rhombus Diagonals</figcaption></figure></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-parallelogram\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><b><strong>Parallelograms</strong></b></a></td><td><span>b \u00d7 h</span></td><td><span>2(l + b)</span></td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Shapes-9\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010323/Shapes-9-100.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010323/Shapes-9.webp 250w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010323/Shapes-9-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010323/Shapes-9-200.webp 200w\" width=\"100\"/><figcaption>Parallelogram dimensions</figcaption></figure></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-trapezium\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><strong>Trapezium</strong></b></a></td><td><span>\u00bd h(a + c)</span></td><td><span>a + b + c + d</span><br/><p dir=\"ltr\"><br/></p><br/></td><td><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Shapes-8\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010322/Shapes-8-100.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010322/Shapes-8.webp 250w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010322/Shapes-8-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230508010322/Shapes-8-200.webp 200w\" width=\"100\"/><figcaption>Trapezium dimensions</figcaption></figure></td></tr></tbody></table><h2 id=\"2d-mensuration-questions-and-answers\" style=\"text-align:left\"><b><strong>Mensuration 2D - Questions and Answers</strong></b></h2><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><b><strong>Q1 : </strong></b><span>Find the perimeter and area of an isosceles triangle whose equal sides are 5 cm and height is 4 cm.\u00a0</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Solution:\u00a0</strong></b></p><blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\"><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">Applying Pythagoras\u2019 theorem,\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">(Hypotenuse)</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> = (Base)</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> + (Height)</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; (5)</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> = (0.5 x Base of isosceles triangle)</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> + (4)</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; 0.5 x Base of isosceles triangle = 3\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; Base of isosceles triangle = 6 cm\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">Therefore, perimeter = sum of all sides = 5 + 5 + 6 = 16 cm\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">Area of triangle = 0.5 x Base x Height = 0.5 x 6 x 4 = 12 cm</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">\u00a0</em></i></p></blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><b><strong>Q2 : </strong></b><span>A rectangular piece of dimension 22 cm x 7 cm is used to make a circle of the largest possible radius. Find the area of the circle formed.\u00a0</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Solution:\u00a0</strong></b></p><blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\"><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">In questions like this, the diameter of the circle is lesser in length and breadth.\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">Here, the breadth Diameter of the circle = 7 cm\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; Radius of the circle = 3.5 cm\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">Therefore, area of the circle = \u03c0 (Radius)</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> = \u03c0 (3.5)</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> = 38.50 cm</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">\u00a0</em></i></p></blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Q3</strong></b><span> : A pizza is to be divided into 8 identical pieces. What would be the angle subtended by each piece at the center of the circle?\u00a0</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Solution:\u00a0</strong></b></p><blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\"><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">By identical pieces, we mean that area of each piece is the same.\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; Area of each piece = (\u03c0 x Radius</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> x \u03b8) / 360 = (1/8) x Area of circular pizza\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; (\u03c0 x Radius</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> x \u03b8) / 360 = (1/8) x (\u03c0 x Radius</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">)\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; \u03b8 / 360 = 1 / 8\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; \u03b8 = 360 / 8 = 45\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">Therefore, the angle subtended by each piece at the center of the circle = 45 degrees\u00a0</em></i></p></blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><b><strong>Q4 : </strong></b><span>Four cows are tied to each corner of a square field of side 7 m. The cows are tied with a rope such that each cow grazes the maximum possible field and all the cows graze in equal areas. Find the area of the ungrazed field.\u00a0</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Solution:\u00a0</strong></b></p><blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\"><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">For maximum and equal grazing, the length of each rope has to be 3.5 cm.\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; Area grazed by 1 cow = (\u03c0 x Radius</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> x \u03b8) / 360\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; Area grazed by 1 cow = (\u03c0 x 3.5</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> x 90) / 360 = (\u03c0 x 3.5</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">) / 4\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; Area grazed by 4 cows = 4 x [(\u03c0 x 3.5</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">) / 4] = \u03c0 x 3.5</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; Area grazed by 4 cows = 38.5 m</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">Now, area of square field = Side</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> = 7</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> = 49 m</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; Area ungrazed = Area of field \u2013 Area grazed by 4 cows\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; Area ungrazed = 49 \u2013 38.5 = 10.5 m</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">\u00a0</em></i></p></blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><b><strong>Q5 : </strong></b><span>Find the area of the largest square that can be inscribed in a circle of radius \u2018r\u2019.\u00a0</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Solution:\u00a0</strong></b></p><blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\"><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">The largest square that can be inscribed in the circle will have the diameter of the circle as the diagonal of the square.\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; Diagonal of the square = 2 r\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; Side of the square = 2 r / 2</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">1/2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">=&gt; Side of the square = 2</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">1/2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> r\u00a0</em></i><br/><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">Therefore, area of the square = Side</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> = [2</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">1/2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> r]</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\"> = 2 r</em></i><i><sup><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">2</em></sup></i><i><em class=\"GFGEditorTheme__textItalic\">\u00a0</em></i></p></blockquote>",
    "sampleTestCases": []
  }
}